LongDescription: Licensee meets requirements for the practice of medicine in California.

Licensee issued a temporary 150-day license for noncompliance with a judgment or order for support. Practice is permitted until the license expiration date. Questions should be directed to the Department of Consumer Affairs' Family Support Unit at (916) 574-8018.

License suspended for noncompliance with a judgment or order for support.  No practice is permitted.  Questions should be directed to the Department of Consumer Affairs' Family Support Unit at (916) 574-8018.

License denied for noncompliance with a judgment or order for support.  No practice is permitted.  Questions should be directed to the Department of Consumer Affairs' Family Support Unit at (916) 574-8018.
License renewal fee has not been paid. No practice is permitted.
License has been voluntarily canceled, or the license has been expired for at least five years and has not been renewed. No practice is permitted.
License is in retired status and the licensee is exempt from payment of the renewal fee. No practice is permitted.

License denied for noncompliance with a judgment or order for support. No practice is permitted. Questions should be directed to the Department of Consumer Affairs' Family Support Unit at (916) 574-8018.
Licensee has voluntarily surrendered the license and the surrender has been accepted by the Board.  No disciplinary action was involved.  No practice is permitted.
Licensee has surrendered his or her license to resolve a disciplinary or licensing action. No practice is permitted.
License has been revoked as a result of disciplinary action rendered by the Board. No practice is permitted.
